dcterms:description: Sea surface temperature (SST) is a fundamental physical variable for understanding, quantifying, and predicting complex interactions between the ocean and atmosphere. Daily analyses of the SST are required by operational numerical weather prediction systems.
dcterms:title: Sea Surface Temperature (SST)

dcterms:description: The Japan Meteorological Agency operates a global ocean data assimilation system to monitor El Niño and Southern Oscillation (ENSO) conditions, providing data for seasonal forecasts and coupled ocean-atmosphere models.
dcterms:title: Japan Meteorological Agency Ocean Data Assimilation System (MOVE, MRI.COM-G2)

dcterms:description: A dataset containing hydrological data relevant for flood inflow forecasting, though specific details are not provided in the paper.
dcterms:title: Hydrological Dataset

dcterms:description: A dataset containing meteorological data used for forecasting purposes, though specific details are not provided in the paper.
dcterms:title: Meteorological Data

dcterms:description: A dataset containing rainfall data relevant for flood inflow forecasting, though specific details are not provided in the paper.
dcterms:title: Rainfall Data
